claim.claim-text:
70. An optical recording and/or reproducing apparatus which records and/or reproduces data from an optical disc which includes recording layers having a lead-in, user data and lead-out areas, wherein each of the lead-in, user data and lead-out areas includes grooves and lands formed thereon, comprising: 
a laser diode which radiates light; 
a collimating lens which collimates the light radiated from the laser diode; 
a polarizing beam splitter which changes a path of the light according to a polarization direction of the light; 
an objective lens which focuses the light onto the optical disc; and 
a photodetector which receives the light uniformly irradiated and reflected from the lead-in, user and lead-out areas having the grooves and the lands formed thereon.
